Rating: 4
Best shortcake ever. I sliced the berries, added a couple of tablespoons of Cointreau (omitted the sugar) to the berries to let them macerate a little. Bakes the shortcakes a day ahead and then popped them in the microwave in paper towels for a few seconds to warm them. Sliced 'em, plopped the berries inside, put the top back on with cream and sat back to rave reviews. What a great recipe.

Rating: 4
The Most Awesome Shortcake Ever! As previous reviewers suggested, I used raw egg yolks, substituted about 1/3 of the flour with cake flour, added about 1/2 teaspoon of salt and one teaspoon of vanilla. What fragrance can possibly beat that of eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla in baked goods? Nothing! These delightful shortcakes seem to be the perfect blend between a cake and a shortbreak cookie. Smell delicious and taste even better!

